Function 13 — settimeout()
Purpose
Sets a time limit on blocking operations. Without a timeout, recv() and accept() wait forever. With a timeout, they raise socket.timeout if nothing happens within the specified seconds.
Syntax
pythonsock.settimeout(seconds)
Parameters
┌──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ seconds  │ Meaning                                          │
├──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ float    │ Wait at most this many seconds                   │
│          │ e.g. 5.0 = 5 seconds                            │
├──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 0        │ Non-blocking mode                                │
│          │ Operations fail instantly if not ready          │
│          │ (raises BlockingIOError)                         │
├──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ None     │ Blocking mode (default)                         │
│          │ Wait forever                                     │
└──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
Three Socket Modes
┌─────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Mode            │ Behavior                                │
├─────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ BLOCKING        │ recv() waits forever for data           │
│ settimeout(None)│ accept() waits forever for client       │
│ (default)       │                                         │
├─────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ TIMEOUT         │ recv() waits up to N seconds            │
│ settimeout(5.0) │ then raises socket.timeout              │
├─────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ NON-BLOCKING    │ recv() returns IMMEDIATELY              │
│ settimeout(0)   │ raises BlockingIOError if no data       │
│ or setblocking  │ Used with select()/asyncio              │
│ (False)         │                                         │
└─────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────┘
Example
pythonsock.settimeout(10.0)   # 10 second timeout

try:
    client_sock, addr = sock.accept()
except socket.timeout:
    print("No client connected within 10 seconds")

