├──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Option               │ What it does                        │
├──────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤
│ SOL_SOCKET           │                                     │
│ SO_REUSEADDR=1       │ Reuse port in TIME_WAIT state       │
│                      │ USE THIS ALWAYS on server sockets   │
├──────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤
│ SOL_SOCKET           │                                     │
│ SO_KEEPALIVE=1       │ Send periodic keep-alive packets    │
│                      │ Detects dead connections            │
├──────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤
│ IPPROTO_TCP          │                                     │
│ TCP_NODELAY=1        │ Disable Nagle's algorithm           │
│                      │ Send data immediately (lower        │
│                      │ latency, used in games/SSH)         │
├──────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤
│ SOL_SOCKET           │                                     │
│ SO_RCVBUF=size       │ Set receive buffer size             │
├──────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤
│ SOL_SOCKET           │                                     │
│ SO_SNDBUF=size       │ Set send buffer size                │
└──────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────┘
What is Nagle's Algorithm?
WITHOUT TCP_NODELAY (Nagle's algorithm ON — default):
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  You send b"H"
  Kernel: "That's tiny. Let me wait 200ms for more data
           so I can bundle it into one packet."
  You send b"i"
  Kernel: "Still small. Waiting..."
  200ms passes
  Kernel sends b"Hi" as one packet.

  GOOD for: bulk file transfer (fewer packets)
  BAD for:  SSH, games, chat (you feel the 200ms delay)


WITH TCP_NODELAY=1:
══════════════════
  You send b"H"  → kernel sends immediately
  You send b"i"  → kernel sends immediately

  GOOD for: interactive applications
  BAD for:  creates more small packets (more overhead)
Example
pythonimport socket

sock = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)

# Must-have for every server:
sock.setsockopt(socket.SOL_SOCKET, socket.SO_REUSEADDR, 1)

# For interactive/chat daemon (disable Nagle):
sock.setsockopt(socket.IPPROTO_TCP, socket.TCP_NODELAY, 1)

# Enable keep-alive:
sock.setsockopt(socket.SOL_SOCKET, socket.SO_KEEPALIVE, 1)

sock.bind(('0.0.0.0', 9000))

